Block VS Inline
	Block : Container elements for grouping , may contain other block of element 
	<div> <h1> <p> <form>

	Inline : Container for text .An inline element does not start on a new line and only takes up as much width as necessary.
	<span> <a> <img>


Table Tag
Caption : table title
Header  : single row for common header
<thead>
</thead>
Body : Multiple rows presenting data
foot : single rows for summary <tfoot> </tfoot>


<tr> table row: required in header footer and body
<th> table header : defines a cell for data in header
<td> table data : defines a cell for data in body and footer

colspan : attributes used on table cells, span across columns and rows
rowspan :

cellspacing : space b/w cells
cellpadding : space between text and cell